201 def configure_from_env(): lppytest

202 """run at startup (on_configure hook)""" 

203 s = {'LP_', 'lp_'} lp

204 LP.set_page_env_vars() lp

205 env_vars = [(f[3:], os.environ[f]) for f in os.environ if f[:3] in s] lp

206 for k, v in env_vars: lp

207 v = lit_prog.cast(v) lp

208 app.debug('From environ', key=k, value=v) lp

209 env_args[k] = v lp

210 LP.stats['LP_env_vars'] = len(env_args) lp

576 def exception(cmd, exc, tb, kw): lppytest

577 c = markdown.Mkdocs.py % {'cmd': cmd, 'kw': kw, 'trb': str(tb)} 

578 app.error('LP evaluation error', exc=exc) 

579 if not LP.on_err_keep_running: 

580 app.die(LP.err_admon, cmd=cmd, lp_file=LP.fn_lp, exc=exc, **kw) 

581 return markdown.Mkdocs.admon(LP.err_admon + ': %s' % str(exc), c, 'error')

583 def confirm(msg, page, cmd, **kw): lppytest

584 if not sys.stdin.isatty(): 

585 app.die('Must have stdin in interactive mode') 

586 app.info(msg, page=page, cmd=cmd, **kw) 

587 print('b=break to enter a pdb debugging session') 

588 print('c=continue to continue non-interactively') 

589 i = input('Continue [Y|n/q|b|c]? ').lower() 

590 if i in ('n', 'q'): 

591 app.die(LP.interrupted) 

592 if i == 'c': 

593 app.info('Continuing without break') 

594 LP.lit_prog_evaluation_step_mode = False 

595 return 

596 if i == 'b': 

597 print('Entering pdb...') 

598 return breakpoint()

654# :docs:patching_mkdocs 

655def patch_mkdocs_to_ignore_res_file_changes(): lppytest

656 """sad. we must prevent mkdocs serve to rebuild each time we write a result file 

657 And we want those result files close to the docs, they should be in that tree. 

658 

659 Also we save tons of rebuilds when preventing to monitor imgs - since often 

660 autocreated, e.g. from kroki or drawio. 

661 """ 

662 import mkdocs 

663 

664 fn = mkdocs.__file__.rsplit('/', 1)[0] 

665 fn += '/livereload/__init__.py' 

666 

667 if not exists(fn): 

668 return app.warning('Cannot patch mkdocs - version mismatch', missing=fn) 

669 

670 s = read_file(fn) 

671 S = 'event.is_directory' 

672 if not S in s: 

673 return app.warning('Cannot patch mkdocs - version mismatch', missing=fn) 

674 if lp_res_ext in s: 

675 return app.info('mkdocs is already patched to ignore %s' % lp_res_ext, fn=fn) 

676 os.system('cp "%s" "%s.orig"' % (fn, fn)) 

677 new = S 

678 for ext in [lp_res_ext, '.svg', '.png']: 

679 new += ' or event.src_path.endswith("%s") ' % ext 

680 new += ' or "/autodocs" in event.src_path ' 

681 # cannot write a comment due to the ':' 

682 s = s.replace(S, new) 

683 write_file(fn, s) 

684 diff = os.popen('diff "%s.orig" "%s"' % (fn, fn)).read().splitlines() 

685 app.info('Diff', json=diff) 

686 msg = ( 

687 'Have patched mkdocs to not watch %s and .svg files. Please restart.' % lp_res_ext 

688 ) 

689 app.die(msg, fn=fn) 

690 # :docs:patching_mkdocs

693def make_plugin_docs(config): lppytest

694 """We want the plugins really self contained, incl. all - also the docs 

695 So we scan whats there and symlink over 

696 """ 

697 

698 def make(pth, dd): lp

699 D = dirname(__file__) + '/plugs' + pth lp

700 dd = config['docs_dir'] + dd lp

701 if not exists(dd): 701 ↛ 702line 701 didn't jump to line 702, because the condition on line 701 was never truelp

702 os.makedirs(dd, exist_ok=True) 

703 

704 c = [] lp

705 for k in sorted(os.listdir(D)): lp

706 # k e.g. 'mermaid' 

707 d = D + '/' + k lp

708 fnr, fnp = d + '/docs/index.md', d + '/__init__.py' lp

709 if not exists(fnr) or not exists(fnp): 709 ↛ 710line 709 didn't jump to line 710, because the condition on line 709 was never truelp

710 continue

802 def on_post_page(self, output, page, config): lppytest

803 """this is intended for side effects outside the html content 

804 Note: at https://github.com/squidfunk/mkdocs-material/issues/2338 only inside 

805 container element is re-evalled at nav.instant events. 

806 """ 

807 fs = getattr(page, 'lp_on_post_page', ()) 

808 for f in fs: 

809 r = f(output=output, page=page, config=config) 

810 output = r or output 

811 return output
